                            <comment id="14632368" author="lhofhansl" created="Sat, 18 Jul 2015 10:45:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So what&apos;s to do here?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The memstore is already not flushed when it is empty (there&apos;s a little bit of preprocessing going on, but that looks pretty lightweight)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;How precise is the last seqid we keep around? Specifically can we instantly tell when onlining a region that there are guaranteed no logs to be replayed even before we split the logs?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;We could allocate mslab lazily perhaps. An unused memstore would then not consume any heap until used.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
